FFDENetwork

Class FFDEServer.InitializationRequestsQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • FFDENetwork.FFDEServer.InitializationRequestsQueue
  • Enclosing class:
    FFDEServer

    private final class FFDEServer.InitializationRequestsQueue
extends java.lang.Object
    This utility class is used to hold requests for kernel until FFDE network reaches state required for them to operate correctly. For example: command "subscribe" will wait until channel feeding subscribed data is available.
